OL,3,CDemocratic oversight measures for NI
OL,4,CBrexit rules are 'insufficient', peers
OL,5,Cfind
OL,7,FA mechanism called the Stormont Brake
OL,8,Fwas also created. That allows a
OL,9,Fminimum of 30 Stormont MLAs, from at
OL,10,Fleast two parties, to refer a proposed
OL,11,FEU law change to the UK Government.
OL,13,FThe Government then makes an
OL,14,Fassessment of the proposed change on
OL,15,FNorthern Ireland and can ultimately
OL,16,Fveto its application in the region.
OL,18,FIf the Government rules that the brake
OL,19,Fhas been appropriately pulled, it must
OL,20,Fthen directly engage with the EU to
OL,21,Ffind a solution.
